<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Partial Info.plist merged into the generated bundle plist by Tauri
  (the CLI auto-detects an `Info.plist` next to tauri.conf.json and merges it,
  for both `tauri dev` and `tauri build`).

  These privacy usage strings are required so that the `claude` CLI — and any
  voice-dictation / speech-to-text helper running inside a session's PTY — can
  reach the microphone. macOS attributes a microphone (or speech-recognition)
  request from a child process to the *responsible* app, i.e. ReCue. Without
  the matching NS*UsageDescription key here, macOS silently denies access and the
  app never even appears under System Settings > Privacy & Security > Microphone
  (which is why voice works in Terminal.app/iTerm2 but not inside ReCue).
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>NSMicrophoneUsageDescription</key>
	<string>ReCue runs agent sessions in the terminal. Microphone access lets the claude CLI and voice-dictation tools you use inside a session capture your voice.</string>
	<key>NSSpeechRecognitionUsageDescription</key>
	<string>ReCue runs agent sessions in the terminal. Speech-recognition access lets voice-dictation tools you use inside a session transcribe your speech into the terminal.</string>
</dict>
</plist>
